parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in transmission recall repairs can cause the motorcycle to become unsafe to ride, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Consumers received recall notices but were unable to have their motorcycles repaired due to a lack of available parts. Dealerships did not have the necessary parts to conduct recall repairs
leaving consumers without a safe and operational vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission recall has caused inconvenience and financial loss to owners, as they are unable to use their motorcycles until the repairs are made.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the motorcycle to stall, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls while driving at a low rate of speed and when the clutch is depressed to stop at a light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank mounting bracket can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to accidents, fires, or environmental hazards.
